==Abstract==

This IIP describes the Bech32m encoding used for INTcoin addresses. It implements BIP 350 for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

Bech32m improves on Bech32 by using a different checksum constant that eliminates a class of errors where certain character substitutions go undetected.

==Specification==

===Checksum Constant===

Bech32m uses constant 0x2bc830a3 instead of Bech32's 0x01.

===Usage===

All INTcoin addresses use Bech32m encoding:
* Witness version 1 (post-quantum): Bech32m

===Encoding===

<pre>
def bech32m_encode(hrp, data):
    values = bech32_hrp_expand(hrp) + data
    checksum = bech32m_create_checksum(hrp, data)
    return hrp + "1" + "".join(CHARSET[v] for v in data + checksum)

def bech32m_create_checksum(hrp, data):
    values = bech32_hrp_expand(hrp) + data
    polymod = bech32_polymod(values + [0,0,0,0,0,0]) ^ BECH32M_CONST
    return [(polymod >> 5*(5-i)) & 31 for i in range(6)]

BECH32M_CONST = 0x2bc830a3
</pre>

===Decoding===

<pre>
def bech32m_decode(addr):
    hrp, data = bech32_decode(addr)
    if bech32_verify_checksum(hrp, data, BECH32M_CONST):
        return hrp, data[:-6]
    return None, None
</pre>

===Error Detection===

Bech32m detects:
* Up to 4 substitution errors
* Any single insertion/deletion
* Most longer error bursts

